<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P. W./7–1545: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 219 <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d219fn1">For the
                                    full text of this message, see <ref target="#d244">document No.
                                        244</ref>.</note></seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-15T18:00:00+01:00">July 15,
                                    1945—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>7146. We were called to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> this
                            afternoon by <persName corresp="#p_HO1">Harvey</persName> who was
                            considerably disturbed about Department’s proposed announcement July 17
                            re <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName> and World Security
                            Organization. …<note n="2" xml:id="d219fn2">See <ref target="#d240">document No. 240</ref>.</note> British Embassy Washington is
                            being instructed to approach Department and request announcement be
                            postponed until the question of future status of <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName> can be discussed at Big Three
                            meeting.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>